casebody.data:
Angello Pete MARIN et al. v. UNITED STATES. No. 8089. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. April 2, 1936. Paul M. Long and F. E. Swope, both of Portland, Or., for appellants. Carl C. Donaugh, U. S. Atty., and M. B. .Strayer; Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Portland, Or.

Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and mandate of this court to be issued forthwith.
